# ABP Studio MCP Tools - AI Usage Guide

ABP Studio exposes 33 MCP tools that let AI interact with the running IDE. These tools give you real-time access to the solution structure, application monitoring, solution runner, Kubernetes/Helm resources, custom commands, and solution modification.

All tools require an open solution in ABP Studio. If no solution is open, every tool returns an error.

## Tool Categories at a Glance

| Category | Purpose | Tools |
|---|---|---|
| Solution Structure | Explore modules, packages, dependencies | `get_solution_info`, `list_modules`, `list_packages`, `get_module_dependencies` |
| Monitoring | Observe running apps (logs, errors, requests) | `list_applications`, `get_exceptions`, `get_logs`, `get_requests`, `get_events`, `clear_monitor` |
| Solution Runner | Start/stop/build apps, containers, tasks | `list_runnable_applications`, `start_application`, `stop_application`, `restart_application`, `build_application`, `list_containers`, `start_containers`, `stop_containers`, `list_tasks`, `run_task`, `stop_task` |
| Run Profiles | Manage profiles and add items | `list_run_profiles`, `select_run_profile`, `create_run_profile`, `add_folder`, `add_dotnet_application`, `add_cli_application`, `add_docker_container` |
| Custom Commands | List and execute user-defined commands | `list_custom_commands`, `run_custom_command` |
| Kubernetes | Explore Helm charts and K8s services | `list_kubernetes_charts`, `list_kubernetes_services` |
| Solution Modifier | Add modules to the solution | `add_microservice_module` |

---

## Workflows

### 1. Understanding a Solution (Start Here)

Always begin with discovery before taking action:

```
get_solution_info          -- solution name, template, module count
  -> list_modules          -- see all modules
  -> list_packages         -- see packages/projects in each module
  -> get_module_dependencies  -- understand how modules connect
```

### 2. Running and Monitoring Applications

```
list_run_profiles           -- see available profiles
  -> select_run_profile     -- switch profile if needed
  -> list_runnable_applications  -- see apps and their current state
  -> start_application      -- start individual or all apps
  -> list_applications      -- see which apps are connected to monitor
  -> get_logs / get_exceptions / get_requests  -- observe runtime behavior
```

After code changes:
```
build_application           -- compile after edits
  -> restart_application    -- restart to pick up changes
  -> get_exceptions         -- check for new errors
```

### 3. Infrastructure (Docker Containers)

```
list_containers             -- see Docker containers in the profile
  -> start_containers       -- docker-compose up (starts all stopped)
  -> stop_containers        -- docker-compose down (stops all running)
```

Containers are typically infrastructure dependencies (databases, Redis, RabbitMQ). Start them before starting applications.

### 4. Running Tasks

Tasks are one-shot operations (database migrations, seed data, npm install, etc.) that run to completion:

```
list_tasks                  -- see available tasks with descriptions
  -> run_task               -- execute and wait for completion (returns exit code + logs)
  -> stop_task              -- cancel if stuck
```

### 5. Executing Custom Commands

Custom commands are user-defined CLI operations. They can target different tree items (Helm charts, K8s services, Solution Runner items):

```
list_custom_commands        -- discover available commands with descriptions, trigger/execution targets
```

Before running a command, find valid targets:
```
list_kubernetes_charts      -- for HelmMainChart / HelmSubChart targets
list_kubernetes_services    -- for KubernetesService targets
list_runnable_applications  -- for SolutionRunnerApplication targets
```

Then run:
```
run_custom_command          -- execute on a specific target, waits for completion, returns logs
```

### 6. Kubernetes Exploration

```
list_kubernetes_charts      -- Helm chart hierarchy (main + sub-charts), metadata, service patterns
list_kubernetes_services    -- K8s services from connected profile, port mappings, interception status
```

Note: `list_kubernetes_services` requires a selected AND connected Kubernetes profile.

### 7. Adding a New Microservice

Only works on microservice-template solutions:

```
get_solution_info           -- verify it's a microservice solution
  -> add_microservice_module  -- creates the service, updates Solution Explorer and Runner
  -> list_tasks             -- find migration tasks for the new service
  -> run_task               -- run database migration
  -> start_application      -- start the new service
```

### 8. Setting Up a Run Profile
```
create_run_profile          -- create empty profile
  -> select_run_profile     -- switch to it
  -> add_folder             -- organize with folders (e.g., "Infrastructure", "Services")
  -> add_docker_container   -- add infrastructure
  -> add_dotnet_application -- add .NET projects
  -> add_cli_application    -- add CLI-based apps
```

