## Quick Reference: Common Scenarios

| User Says | Tool Sequence |
|---|---|
| "Start the application" | `list_runnable_applications` -> `start_application` |
| "What errors are happening?" | `list_applications` -> `get_exceptions` |
| "Run database migration" | `list_tasks` -> `run_task` |
| "Deploy to Kubernetes" | `list_custom_commands` -> `list_kubernetes_charts` -> `run_custom_command` |
| "Add a new service" | `get_solution_info` -> `add_microservice_module` |
| "Show me the API calls" | `list_applications` -> `get_requests` |
| "Build and restart" | `build_application` -> `restart_application` |
| "Start infrastructure" | `list_containers` -> `start_containers` |
| "What does this solution look like?" | `get_solution_info` -> `list_modules` -> `list_packages` |
| "Check application logs" | `get_logs` with `app` and optionally `level: "Error"` |

---

## Error Handling

All tools return structured responses. Error responses include an `isError: true` flag and a descriptive message. Common error patterns:

- **"No solution is open"** -- The user needs to open a solution in ABP Studio first
- **"No run profile selected"** -- Use `list_run_profiles` and `select_run_profile`
- **"Application not found"** -- Use the list tool to get exact names
- **"Kubernetes profile not connected"** -- The user needs to connect the K8s profile in the UI first
- **"Timed out"** -- Increase `timeout_seconds` or check if the operation is stuck
